    <item>
      <title>Two AAs I see that a lot of tanks lack and tis not a good thing.</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&amp;message.id=12539#M12539</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;When I play my 70 Cleric or Shaman, I notice alot ( about 80%) of the tanks I buff whether they be Paly, SK or Warrior do not have enough buff slots open. I explain to them that "Mystical Attuning " is a very good AA to have its 5 levels allowing more buffs to be cast on you up to 20 buff slots, this is especially important with a Bard in the group or a Cleric casting Panolpy of Vie&amp;nbsp; and Hots or a Shaman casting Leopard or Ferine Avatar. Most reply it is a waste of time and is low on their priority of AAs to get. I disagree.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Another AA I notice alot of Warriors lacking in is "Weapons Affinity" which is 5 levels and allows your weapons to proc more frequently, this is especially beneficial when the warrior is trying to hold agro. Some Warriors I talk to think this is another low priority AA, once again I disagree.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Odd but the truly good tanks and epecially the well geared tanks I have grouped with all agree on the benefits of Weapons Affinity and Mystical attuning. The not so good tanks are going for weapon crits and reflexive mastery. Now reflex is a very good AA for defensive but really should be balanced out with other AAs. Not having a buff slot open for Spirit of Sense (improved less hits on you by mob) and PoV that mitigates damage will be detrimental to the not so well geared tank.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Frankly my 70 Warrior has&amp;nbsp;gets more benfits from Sos and Pov than filling out his last DoD reflexive mastery AAs, (though he is working on then). I have found that a tank performs better if he has open slots for HoTs, PoV, SoS and Leopard. Just my opinion.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
