      <title>Re: Two AAs I see that a lot of tanks lack and tis not a good thing.</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&amp;message.id=16011#M16011</link>
      <description>This is a mixed bag in my opinion. It depends in part on your character, your gear, your playing style, and the zones you visit.&lt;br&gt;MA is useless for me. WA is an absolute must.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I for instance have no use whatsoever for MA with my warrior at this time. This however is because I have spent a lot of time in the 60-66 range raising defensive aa's getting better gear, and augments. I do not think I have ever had need for more than 5 buffs on my warrior since lvl 60. This is because all melee stats are maxed via gear/augments, and because I can't use the required lvl 70 augments that give me better abilities. As a result, all of those stat buffs are worthless to me, unless I can get one that increases my max stats, and that's still only 1 or 2 buffs, and I seldom have the opportunity to group with individuals who have those buffs regardless. Therefore, I'm frequently running around with 2-3 buffs at most, unless in a raid, and even then it's usually only 4-5 buffs. So I'm nowhere close to needing more buff slots, so why waste the aa's on them now (that's a fair chunk of time/aa's for buff slots I wouldn't use)? I get far more bang for the buck getting more defensives, and offensives. My warrior just made 66 a couple of days ago, and with his normal virtue, or if I'm lucky a conviction (usually his only buffs) I'm still over 9k hps and 1.7k AC, this is more than adequate to tank the mobs that I'm going after in WoS, lower GoD zones, and a large chunk of PoP. (Stack Vie, HoT's and I'm up to a whopping 3 buffs!! 4 if there's a haster along) True, I've got 150-odd AA's, almost exclusively in Defensives, and HP's with a couple in utility aa's such as AE taunt, and WA5. You just need to be careful with blanket statements like this though, because there are a lot of variables that impact a tank's ability to take on mobs. I admit that leveling to 70 with no aa's and not very good gear would make MA very important. My level 65 Beastlord for instance is almost always maxed out on buffs(despite having 250 aa's), and needs to get MA next very badly, but my warrior most definitely does not need it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
