      <title>Re: Two AAs I see that a lot of tanks lack and tis not a good thing.</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&amp;message.id=12555#M12555</link>
      <description>&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
ChillaWinda wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;When I play my 70 Cleric or Shaman, I notice alot ( about 80%) of the tanks I buff whether they be Paly, SK or Warrior do not have enough buff slots open. I explain to them that "Mystical Attuning " is a very good AA to have its 5 levels allowing more buffs to be cast on you up to 20 buff slots, this is especially important with a Bard in the group or a Cleric casting Panolpy of Vie&amp;nbsp; and Hots or a Shaman casting Leopard or Ferine Avatar. Most reply it is a waste of time and is low on their priority of AAs to get. I disagree.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Another AA I notice alot of Warriors lacking in is "Weapons Affinity" which is 5 levels and allows your weapons to proc more frequently, this is especially beneficial when the warrior is trying to hold agro. Some Warriors I talk to think this is another low priority AA, once again I disagree.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Odd but the truly good tanks and epecially the well geared tanks I have grouped with all agree on the benefits of Weapons Affinity and Mystical attuning. The not so good tanks are going for weapon crits and reflexive mastery. Now reflex is a very good AA for defensive but really should be balanced out with other AAs. Not having a buff slot open for Spirit of Sense (improved less hits on you by mob) and PoV that mitigates damage will be detrimental to the not so well geared tank.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Frankly my 70 Warrior has&amp;nbsp;gets more benfits from Sos and Pov than filling out his last DoD reflexive mastery AAs, (though he is working on then). I have found that a tank performs better if he has open slots for HoTs, PoV, SoS and Leopard. Just my opinion.&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I will admit I don't have Mystical Attuning. I do have most the other's that have been talked about on this thread though. The reason I don't have Mystical attuning yet, is mainly because I work on my AA's in a "Needy" matter. I found myself lacking in the defensive, cleric's having to actually ask for a second to med, etc. I improved that, then had a problem with aggro (as I was in higher content, and was against higher then even con mobs), and decided to work on aggro AA's (The one's listed by TSW). Doing the Aggro AA's greatly improved my DPS as well, so I had found a two way benefit on this. My proc'ing AA's maxed, etc. Then I decided I needed AE taunt (I know, should have got it sooner, but didn't find myself needing it till I started having to pull... ADDS, lol). &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Adding more buff slot's for the majority of time, isn't on my highest of priority list, since I don't normally have over maximum buffs on me at one time anyways. I ussually have over 3 to 5 slot's left, and if I need one, I can take one off that is less needed. To me, it's one of them Nice to have AA's, but not a "game breaker" in my need for AA's. I have over 240, and have only broke into a small chunk of what there is, untill I either max my aggro and defensive AA's, or find them no longer a problem for the content I do, I won't be trying for more buff slots. &lt;/P&gt;</description>
